metadata.name: Unsquare composition #41
metadata.description:
Inspired by Jazz, Unsquare composition I experiments with the notion of non-squared rhythmic forms, where freedom and improvisation take as a premise the idea of an imperfection where we can also find harmony. 

Please do not expect perfect results.

unknowable 2022


Usage
press [s] - save .png

metadata.name: Brutalist #164
metadata.description:
from the depth
the architect ponder
reshape my world
in hollow order

#11
experimental vintage series

press "C" to turn on/off outlines
press "V" to turn on/off background objects and grid, if any present
press "B" to turn on/off rotation
press "N" to reload with different layout, 3 iterations to cycle through

press "UP arrow" to increase render scale multiplier by x1 (maximum is x4, default is x3)
press "DOWN arrow" to decrease render scale multiplier by x1 (minimum is x1)

press "S" to save png in live view

metadata.name: Mandatory Destiny #102
metadata.description:
"Mandatory Destiny" is the fifth collection released as a part of NeoMent's "Abandoned Reality" series.

It is impossible for everyone to be equal. Too much of a person is defined by random chance. The country they were born in, the financial situation of their family, even their genetics. If someone was unlucky and has low natural IQ, they can't change it. And it affects their life significantly. If someone was born in a poor country or family, it might be extremely harder to get a good education, and later, a well-paying job. Some people are fortunate enough to get a headstart, while others aren't so lucky.

The only way for everyone to be truly equal would be identical starting conditions, and that's utterly impossible to achieve.

metadata.name: Penumbra #163
metadata.description:
Penumbra is a geometric exploration of the possible outcomes from 3 basic rules:

1) Place some walls
2) Place some light sources
3) Draw the resulting shadows

This series is a small thank you to the collectors of Umbra :)
